events.text:
Teaching: Prof. Dr. Peter Kneisel and Prof. Dr. Axel Schumann
Description: Students learn the essential standards for presenting information on the Internet. They have basic knowledge of web programming and can develop simple client-side programs.
Room: A10.6.06
Recommended attributes: Knowledge and Will

events.choice: ( Look at 'Basics and usage of social media' )

events.text:
Teaching: Jelena Volkwein-Mogel and Prof. Dr. Julie Dolores Woletz
Description: The course teaches central theories of communication and media research with a focus on digital/social media.
Students learn theoretical and methodological principles for the user-centered development of digital media and apply them in a practical media project.
Room: A10.8.20
Recommended attributes: Creativity and Dexterity
